# Step 1: Import data
qs_data <- read.csv("QS World University Rankings 2025 (Top global universities).csv", encoding = "ISO-8859-1")

# Step 3: Clean and select only numeric score columns
qs_data_clean <- qs_data %>%
  select(Overall_Score,
         Academic_Reputation_Score,
         Employer_Reputation_Score,
         Faculty_Student_Score,
         Citations_per_Faculty_Score,
         International_Faculty_Score,
         International_Students_Score,
         International_Research_Network_Score,
         Employment_Outcomes_Score,
         Sustainability_Score) %>%
  mutate(across(everything(), ~as.numeric(as.character(.)))) %>%
  drop_na()  # Remove rows with NA values

# Step 5: Correlation matrix
cor_matrix <- cor(qs_data_clean)
corrplot(cor_matrix, method = "color", type = "upper", tl.col = "black")

# Step 6: Scatterplot matrix
ggpairs(qs_data_clean)

# Step 7: Train-test split
set.seed(123)
train_index <- createDataPartition(qs_data_clean$Overall_Score, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
train_data <- qs_data_clean[train_index, ]
test_data <- qs_data_clean[-train_index, ]

# Step 8: Fit the model (Linear regression)
lm_model <- lm(Overall_Score ~ ., data = train_data)
summary(lm_model)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Overall_Score ~ ., data = train_data)

# Step 9: Check for multicollinearity (Variance Inflation Factor)
vif(lm_model)

##                             4.768710                             3.495764

##                 Sustainability_Score 
##                             1.925726
# Step 10: Residual diagnostics (plots)
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
plot(lm_model)

# Step 11: Predict on test set
predictions <- predict(lm_model, newdata = test_data)

# Step 12: Evaluate model
actuals <- test_data$Overall_Score
mae <- mean(abs(predictions - actuals))
rmse <- sqrt(mean((predictions - actuals)^2))
r_squared <- 1 - sum((actuals - predictions)^2) / sum((actuals - mean(actuals))^2)

cat("MAE:", mae, "\n")
## MAE: 0.02535806
cat("RMSE:", rmse, "\n")
## RMSE: 0.02911182
cat("R-squared:", r_squared, "\n")
## R-squared: 0.9999973
# Step 13: Plot predicted vs actual
ggplot(data = NULL, aes(x = actuals, y = predictions)) +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue") +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(title = "Predicted vs Actual Overall Scores",
       x = "Actual Overall Score",
       y = "Predicted Overall Score") +
  theme_minimal()
